<br>
If you're not doing tasks, I suggest doing them.  I was able to afford some new armor after doing them, plus I leveled a lot faster than I would have soloing yellows with my pet. <p><B>Salicia Swiftfoot<BR> 10 <I>Druid of Hibernia, Palomides Server</I><br>Proud Member of <a href=http://pub33.ezboard.com/bdaocdivine>Divine</a><br>DAoC Moderator for <a href=http://thedruidsgrove.org/>The Druids Grove</a></B><br><br> Click <a href="http://divineguildpics.homestead.com/Memorial.html"> here</a> to read the last EQ story of Salicia Swiftfoot.<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueckointhedarkness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ecko in the darkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/26/01 10:54:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=138.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tasks - an easy way to get xp from 1 to 20</span><hr size=1>   Level 17 Search and Destroy task by Meara in Mag Mell nets 144856 exp.  Did 3 in 20 minutes only because I was burnt out on Parth group I did earlier in the day.   <br>
  1. Bear forager  2. Roane Maiden.  3. Raone companion 4. Crum poacher yet to do.<br>
  <br>
   Sometimes it can go all your way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usanterre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santerre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/26/01 11:18:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=138.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tasks - an easy way to get xp from 1 to 20</span><hr size=1> It was my experience that I gained an equal amount of XP and far more cash soloing low blue/green mobs as a hero.  This is due to the very minimal downtime associated with killing low cons.  However, my bard friends did much of their levelling 1-20 doing tasks, and still continue to do quests for xp.<br>
<br>
Remember the number of tasks you can do per level is limited. <p><BR><br><B><I><img src="http://www.druidmail.com/santerre2.gif">Santerre.</I></B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustryhf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stryhf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/26/01 12:07:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=138.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tasks - an easy way to get xp from 1 to 20</span><hr size=1> I was able to get a blademaster to level 10 within 3 hours of /played time.  This was by max'ing out the kill tasks per level and doing whatever associated quests were available.  By 10th level, I had a good set of Reinforced armor which con's yellow to me, as well as 2 weapons which con'ed yellow to me, and a sizable chunk of cash left over to start him as a weaponsmith (approximately 70silver).  This was w/o any twinking or additional cash.<br>
<br>
The main thing about tasks to remember is that once you find someone who will give you kill tasks for that level, that will continue to do so until you level or you reach your maximum tasks per level limit.  There are 4 NPC's within the Ardee/Mag Mell area which will give out kill tasks, and what they ask you to kill is well within a short running distance.<br>
<br>
Tasks are a great way to alleviate some of the boredom of just kill, kill, kill.  In much the same way that I've found consignments help in breaking the monotony of trying to raise tradeskills.<br>
